wrote:
>
> In rethinking your suggestion - "send an editable version" - I couldn't
remember why you needed one.  Do you still have the original, and if so,
isn't that editable? And if not, I'll send another, but does it matter to
you whether it's Word or pdf?
>
> I liked your example, by the way.  After all these years, it still brings
back vivid memories.
>
> Richard
>
> On Friday, January 1, 2021, 10:06:20 AM PST, Josh Klein <josh@josh.is>
wrote:
>
>
> Read it. Loved it. Lots there; some of it more noise than signal, but
several of these pieces hit that nerve of recognized truth, like a kid's
loose tooth or a knock to your funny bone. As you quoted me, there is
definitely a there there.
>
> My first, practical suggestion is to go through them to improve the
signal quotient. If you can settle on a format (and my suspicion is that it
is a short paragraph of observation vs. fiction or poetry or story) then it
becomes a question of repeatability and distribution, which are
discoverable quantities.
>
> I would also note that "settle on a format" here really means "find a way
to love and distill."
>
> Looking forward to speaking again,
> Josh

> =E1=90=A7

